| Complete Security Awareness Training | HR/Security | | Per Security Awareness Training Program |
| Background check completed (where applicable) | HR | | Per Background Check Policy |

5. Tools access (Kahana-specific)
New hires receive access to tools relevant to their function, including but not limited to:
- Google Workspace (email, docs, calendar)
- Slack / Discord (internal communication)
- GitHub (for engineering)
- Tally.so, Google Sheets (feedback, sprints)
- Oasis (product; install as default browser)
- AWS, Supabase (for engineering/DevOps, per Access Control Policy)

Access is granted per least privilege; MFA required where supported.

6. Evidence for SOC 2
- Completed checklist with sign-off (electronic)
- Policy acknowledgment records
- Security training completion record
- Access request/approval records

7. Review and Maintenance
This checklist is reviewed at least annually and updated when onboarding process or tools change. Aligns with data room: https://data-room-two.vercel.app/onboarding
